        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 10:00AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 959 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Fort Davis, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Balmorhea Lake and Star Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
